what is generic class?
We use a Generic Repository so that we don't have to write the same CRUD operations for every entity. Instead of creating separate repositories for Employee, Product, Customer, etc., we create a single generic repository that 
works with any entity type. This reduces code duplication, improves reusability, and makes the code easier to maintain.
A Generic Class is a reusable class that uses a type parameter (T) instead of a fixed data type. This allows the same class to work with different types or entities. 
In my project, we used a Generic Repository so that one repository implementation could perform common CRUD operations for different entities like Employee, Product, and Customer, 
instead of creating separate repository classes for each entity.
This improves code reusability, reduces duplication, and makes the application easier to maintain.

