static readonly is a runtime constant shared by all objects of a class. It is initialized once during declaration or in the static constructor and cannot be modified afterward.
var is a compile-time feature where the compiler automatically determines the variable's type from the assigned value.

dynamic is a runtime feature where type checking is performed during execution instead of at compile time.
