What are Extension Methods?
Extension methods allow us to add new methods to existing data types (without modifying their original code), and we can use them anywhere in the application — as long as we import the namespace where the 
extension method is defined, using the using directive.
using System;

public static class Event
{
    public static bool checkEven(this int num)
    {
        return num % 2 == 0;
    }
}

public class HelloWorld
{
